1. How to display images in title bar?
   Majority of wesites add icon or image logo in the title bar. The icon logo is called favicon. Using following steps images an be displayed in the title
   bar:
   i. Choose the image and upload the file to the host directory.
   ii. Specify the image you want to use as a favicon in the code of the website. Add the following link to your <head> section:
       <head>
        <link rel="icon" href="icon.jpg">
       </head>  

2.  What is the purpose of "alt" attribute of img tag?
    It specifies an alternate text for an image, if the image cannot be displayed. 
